{
  "text": "Let's create a network stack that exports VPC and subnet information. This stack will contain all our networking resources, VPC, subnets, Internet Gateway, NAT Gateway, and route tables. We export the VPC ID, subnet IDs, and security group IDs so other stacks can reference them. This separation of concerns allows you to manage networking separately from application resources. The network stack becomes a foundation that other stacks build upon.",
